FORMS

***Access Forms Using JS--Form sırasına göre javascripten referans:

document.forms[0]; // the first form
document.forms[1]; // the second form

  <form name="form1 / form2">
document.forms.form1; // the first form
document.forms.form2; // the second form

***Submitting
<button type="submit">Submit</button>
<button type="reset">Reset form data</button>
<button type="button">Do something</button>
----
<form name="myForm">
    <span>Only users that are 18 and over can visit the website</span> 
  <input name="age" type="number" placeholder="Enter your age">
  <button type="submit">Let me in</button>
</form>
const form = document.forms.myForm; // getting a form
                                                          // binding an event handler of the submit event to the form
form.addEventListener("submit", function (evt) {
  evt.preventDefault();   // let's cancel the default action that belongs to the event
  // checking the user data  // evt.preventDefault() called the form won't be submitted and the page won't be refreshed.
});

***Sending Data to the server
-- action attribute 
<form name="form" action="https://myserverdomain.com/form-handler">   -- old way

